description:
Joining Mirabaud, means entering an entrepreneurial and innovative environment. With the 7th generation of the Mirabaud family working within the bank, the culture is that of a family business. With over 700 employees based in 10 countries worldwide, Mirabaud offers opportunities to develop one’s career across an international network of 16 offices.

DATA ANALYST

Risk & Compliance

A day in your future job:

The Data Analyst is responsible for the analysis, creation and maintenance of reports used for decision-making, control, analysis, and visualization of information in the organization.

The Data Analyst is also in charge of the support to the users of the implemented reports.
• Execution and monitoring of data processing and reporting related to the activity of Risk & Compliance ;
• Development of Risk and Compliance monitoring and analysis tools;
• Maintenance of legacy reporting applications (VBA, Access, Excel);
• Participation in the project to overhaul the current banking... system towards a new banking platform;
• Analysis and development of extractions to meet new business requirements;
• Deployment, training and support to users in the context of change management.

Your assets to succeed:
• Minimum 4 years of experience in the field of information development;
• Significant experience in the banking sector, preferably in the field risk & compliance;
• Degree in computer science or with equivalent professional experience;
• Knowledge and mastery of BI tools (e.g. Power BI);
• Good understanding of Database models and query languages such as SQL;
• Proficiency in MS Office tools, good knowledge of VBA;
• Fluent in French and English, knowledge of another language is an asset;
• Curious, service-minded, structured and analytical;
• Proactive and solution-oriented.

Jump on the boat!
• Family-friendly and dynamic environment;
• Direct impact on the business, no matter your position or seniority;
• Work in an environment that encourages autonomy and entrepreneurship;
• Flexible working arrangements to help you achieve a better work-life balance;
• Variety of cultural and sporting activities during your free time;
• Inclusion and equal treatment;
• Various employee benefits & family friendly benefits.

Notes:

Only candidates with a suitable profile will receive a response, thank you for your understanding.

We will not accept any CVs from agency

