description:
ADP Clear PTE LTD is a technology start-up majority owned by Mercuria Energy Group, one of the world's largest commodity trading companies. ADP Clear operates as a solutions provider to the global bunkering industry and related staekholders. We operate a global technology team, running an agile delivery model with a focus on automation, optimization, innovation, and control.

The Advanced Delivery Platform (ADP) is an innovative solution comprised of integrated hardware and software that provides a completely transparent and efficient bunker delivery service, reducing cost and risk for customers.

ADP is a multi-party workflow platform which digitises the bunker requisition process from start to finish. Bunker suppliers using ADP can manage their digital bunker supplies, including electronic documentation, e-signatures, and bunker delivery data. Bunker buyers can have access to all their delivery data and documents, rely on automated notifications from their suppliers, increased... transparency on product delivered and higher efficiency of operations.

Responsibilities:
• Work closely with business users to understand processes, document workflows, and capture requirements;
• Speak on an even level with key business stakeholders and technology partners;
• Actively seek to identify and drive improvements and innovation;
• Acquire business knowledge and system knowledge to further individual development;
• Support the product owner to prioritize roadmap, define scope of features and user stories;
• Test and validate software enhancements prior to deployments;
• Create internal and external system documentation;
• Work with design team on user experience and wireframing;
• Work with development team to ensure successful delivery of ADP product streams through an agile framework.

Job Profile:
• Over 3 years of experience working with product development on an agile framework;
• Knowledge of product management tools such as DevOps, Notion, Figma would be advantageous;
• Subject matter expertise in at least one area of a commodity organisations operating model, with bunkering being advantageous but not essential;
• Strong expertise in writing requirements in the form of user stories within an Agile delivery model;
• Experience building project plans, documentation, and reporting progress;
• Strong understanding of data models;
• Strong analytical skills and ability to interpret complex data sets;
• Comfortable with ambiguity and autonomy, but enjoy working within a dynamic, fast-paced, and fast-changing environment.

You may apply directly through LinkedIn or send your CV, with the position title in the subject of your email, directly to recruitment@mercuria.com

